5: OFFSET
============

Har Partition ke andar har message ko ek unique Offset milta hai.

Offset ek continuously increasing number (index) hota hai jo us Partition
ke andar message ki position ko uniquely identify karta hai.

--------------
## IMPORTANT:
--------------

Offset sirf apne Partition ke andar unique hota hai.

Alag-alag Partitions me same Offset number exist kar sakta hai.

------------
## EXAMPLE:
------------

Maan lo Producer ne messages:

A, B, C, D aur E

isi sequence me publish kiye hain.

Suppose:

Topic : "my-topic"

Is Topic ke paas sirf 1 Partition hai.

Partition-0
|
|- Offset 0 -> A
|- Offset 1 -> B
|- Offset 2 -> C
|- Offset 3 -> D
|- Offset 4 -> E

Kyuki Topic me sirf ek hi Partition hai, isliye saare messages
sequentially isi Partition me store honge.

Jaise-jaise naye messages publish hote jayenge, Kafka unhe
Partition ke end me append karta jayega aur har naye message ko
agla Offset assign karta jayega.

Example:

Sabse pehle A publish hua, isliye usse Offset 0 mila.

A ke baad B publish hua, isliye usse Offset 1 mila.

B ke baad C publish hua, isliye usse Offset 2 mila.

Aur isi tarah:

D -> Offset 3

E -> Offset 4


