## HOW KAFKA HANDLES OFFSET MANAGEMENT, HEARTBEATS, REBALANCING & PARTITION ASSIGNMENT FOR STANDALONE CONSUMERS
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## IMPORTANT
--------------

Kafka committed offsets ko hamesha group.id ke context me store karta hai. 

Kafka kabhi bhi offsets ko kisi individual Consumer ke naam se store nahi karta.

Isliye Offset Commit ke liye Consumer Group identity (group.id) hona zaruri hai.

Standalone Consumer ke paas group.id configured hone se wo Consumer Group ka member nahi ban jata.

group.id sirf Offset Commit ke context me use hota hai.

Consumer Group ka member banne ke liye Consumer ko subscribe() API use karke Consumer Group join karna padta hai.

Heartbeat, Rebalancing aur Automatic Partition Assignment sirf Consumer Groups (subscribe() API) ke liye hote hain.


## CASE-1
-----------

Maan lo Standalone Consumer manually Partition assign karta hai:

consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(
    new TopicPartition("orders", 0)
));

Aur uske paas:

group.id=my-app

configured hai.

Ab ye Consumer manually Partition assign kar raha hai, isliye ye Consumer Group
join nahi karega.

Is wajah se:

- Kafka automatic Partition Assignment nahi karega.
- Heartbeats nahi hongi.
- Rebalancing nahi hogi.

Lekin kyunki group.id configured hai, isliye jab Consumer messages process karke Offset Commit karega,
to Kafka us Committed Offset ko us Consumer Group ke liye
apne __consumer_offsets internal topic me store kar lega.

Sirf group.id configure kar dene se offsets automatically commit nahi honge. Consumer ko offsets commit karne ke liye ya to Auto Commit enable karna hoga ya phir Manual Commit use karna hoga.

Offset Commit do tariko se ho sakta hai:

## 1. Auto Commit

enable.auto.commit = true

Ya

## 2. Manual Commit

consumer.commitSync();

Ya

consumer.commitAsync();


Consumer restart hone par Kafka Committed Offset check karega
aur uske next Offset se reading continue karwa dega.


## CASE-2
-----------

Ab maan lo Standalone Consumer manually Partition assign karta hai:

consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(
    new TopicPartition("orders", 0)
));

Lekin is baar:

group.id

configured nahi hai.

Ab kyunki Kafka ke paas koi Consumer Group identity hi nahi hai,
isliye Kafka uske Offsets automatically commit ya store nahi kar sakta.

Is wajah se:

- Kafka automatic Partition Assignment nahi karega.
- Heartbeats nahi hongi.
- Rebalancing nahi hogi.
- Auto Commit aur Manual Commit (commitSync()/commitAsync()) bhi use nahi kiye ja sakte. 
  i.e Offsets maintain karne ki responsibility application ki hoti hai.


Example:

Database:

orders
|
Partition-0
|
Committed Offset = 125

Ya:

Redis :

Partition-0 -> Offset = 125


Ya:

File

Partition-0 -> Offset = 125

Consumer restart hone par application isi stored Offset ko read karegi
aur uske next Offset se reading continue karwayegi.

