9: WHY PARTITIONS ARE REQUIRED IN A TOPIC?
============================================

------------------
1: SCALABILITY
------------------

Maan lo ek Topic hai:

Orders

Aur usme continuously messages aa rahe hain:

Message-1
Message-2
Message-3
...
Message-10 Billion

Agar Topic ka saara data sirf ek hi Broker par store ho raha ho:

Broker-1
|
Orders Topic


To time ke saath messages badhte jaayenge aur ek point par:

- Broker ki storage limit reach ho sakti hai.
- Broker ki processing capacity limit reach ho sakti hai.
- Broker ke hardware resources (CPU, Memory, Disk) bottleneck ban sakte hain.

Is problem ko solve karne ke liye Kafka Topic ko multiple Partitions me divide karta hai.


## EXAMPLE:

Orders Topic
|
|- Partition-0
|- Partition-1
|- Partition-2

Ab in Partitions ko alag-alag Brokers par distribute kiya ja sakta hai:

Broker-1 -> Partition-0
Broker-2 -> Partition-1
Broker-3 -> Partition-2

Isse Topic ka data multiple Brokers me spread ho jata hai aur system horizontally scale kar pata hai.

Isliye Partitions Kafka ko large amount of data handle karne aur system ko efficiently scale karne me help karte hain.


----------------------
2: PARALLEL PROCESSING
----------------------

Agar Kafka me Topics ke andar Partitions na hote aur har Topic sirf ek single entity hoti, to us Topic ka data sirf ek hi stream ki tarah consume kiya ja sakta tha.

Is situation me kisi bhi Topic ka data parallel process karna possible nahi hota.

But sirf Partitions bana dene se parallel processing automatically start nahi ho jaati.

Parallel processing ka actual benefit Consumer Groups provide karte hain.

Consumer Group Topic ke Partitions ko apne Consumers ke beech divide kar deta hai, jisse multiple Consumers alag-alag Partitions ko simultaneously consume kar sakte hain.


## IMPORTANT:
---------------

Consumer Groups parallel processing tabhi achieve kar sakte hain jab Topic me multiple Partitions available hon.

Agar Topic me sirf ek hi Partition hai, to Consumer Group me chahe kitne bhi Consumers hon, us Partition ko sirf ek hi Consumer consume karega aur baaki Consumers idle rahenge.

Isliye:

Partitions parallelism ko enable karte hain,

aur Consumer Groups us parallelism ko efficiently utilize karte hain.


==================
9: REPLICATION
==================

Kafka replication use karta hai, jisme har partition ki multiple replicas different brokers par distribute ki ja sakti hain. 
Ek replica Leader hoti hai aur baaki replicas Followers hoti hain
Leader replica read / write requests handle karti hai, aur follower replicas continuously leader se data copy karti rehti hain, 
taaki fault tolerance aur high availability ensure ki ja sake.

