12 : ACKS Kya Hai?
=====================

Maan lo Kafka cluster me multiple brokers hain:

Broker-1
Broker-2
Broker-3

Topic = Alphabet

Topic ke paas sirf 1 Partition hai:

Alphabet
|
|- Partition-0

 
Aur Replication Factor = 3 hai.

Matlab Partition-0 ki total 3 copies (replicas) hongi jo different brokers
par store hongi.

Partition Distribution:

Broker-1 -> Partition-0 (Leader)
Broker-2 -> Partition-0 (Follower)
Broker-3 -> Partition-0 (Follower)


Producer message bhejta hai: "A"

Jo Partition-0 ke Leader Replica (Broker-1) me store hota hai.

Uske baad Followers (In Broker-2 and Broker-3) Leader se data copy karenge.

i.e

Current State:

Leader Offset = 0 (Broker-1)

Follower-1 Offset = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset = 0 (Broker-3)


Question:

Leader replica producer ko kab bolega:

"Message Successfully Stored"

Iska answer ACKS configuration deta hai.

'acks' Producer-side setting hai.

Producer decide karta hai:

"Mujhe success kab maana hai?"

-------------------
Case 1: ACKS = 0
-------------------

Producer message publish karne ke baad bina kisi confirmation from Leader Replica (i.e. Partition-0 in Broker-1)
ka wait kiye aage badh jata hai i.e Producer wait hi nahi karta after publishing the message.

Advantage:
Fastest

Disadvantage:

Agar network issue hua:

Producer ----X----> Leader

To message gaya bhi ya nahi gaya,
producer ko pata nahi.

Data loss possible.

-------------------
Case 2: ACKS = 1
-------------------

Producer message publish karta hai ye message Partition-0 ke Leader Replica (i.e. Partition-0 in Broker-1)
ke paas jata hai.

Leader replica receive karta hai.

Leader replica disk par write karta hai.

Fir Producer ko ACK bhej deta hai.

Important:

Followers ne copy kiya ya nahi,
Producer ko koi farak nahi padta.

Bas Leader ne successfully write kar liya ho.

## PROBLEM:

Current State:

Leader Offset = 0 (Broker-1)

Follower-1 Offset = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset = 0 (Broker-3)

Producer ne ek naya message bheja manlo "B"

Leader replica us message ko write kar deta hai:

Now 
Leader replica Offset = 1

Aur Producer ko ACK bhej deta hai.

Producer: SUCCESS

Lekin ussi second Leader crash ho gaya.

Followers tak Offset 1 wala message i.e "B"
abhi replicate hi nahi hua tha.

Current State:

Follower-1 Offset = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset = 0 (Broker-3)

ISR = {Follower-1, Follower-2}


## IMPORTANT NOTE:
-------------------

ISR me hone ka matlab ye nahi hai ki replica har moment
Leader ke exact same Offset par hi ho.

ISR replicas thoda lag kar sakte hain,
lekin wo Leader ke sufficiently close aur synchronized maane jaate hain.

Ab Kafka ISR me se naya Leader elect karega.

Suppose:

Follower-1 (Partition-0 in Broker-2)

new Leader ban gaya.

## RESULT:
-----------

Offset 101 wala message kisi replica tak pahucha hi nahi tha.

Isliye Offset 101 wala message lost ho gaya.

Data Loss.


--------------------
Case 3: ACKS = ALL
--------------------

Current State:

Leader Offset      = 0 (Broker-1)

Follower-1 Offset  = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset  = 0 (Broker-3)

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}


Producer message publish karta hai.

Ye message Partition-0 ke Leader Replica (i.e. Partition-0 on Broker-1) ke paas jata hai.

Leader replica receive karta hai.

Leader replica disk par message write karta hai.

Ab Leader replica wait karega.

Jab tak ye message sabhi ISR replicas tak replicate nahi ho jata.

Uske baad hi Producer ko ACK bheja jayega.

## EXAMPLE:

Producer ne ek naya message bheja: "B"

Leader replica us message ko write kar deta hai.

Updated State:

Leader replica Offset = 1


Ab Leader replica (Partition-0 on Broker-1) wait karega jab tak baaki ISR replicas (Partition-0 on Broker-2 and Broker-3)
bhi is message ko write na kar lein.

Final State:

Leader Offset      = 1
Follower-1 Offset  = 1
Follower-2 Offset  = 1


Ab Kafka Producer ko ACK bhej dega.


## KYA ACKS = ALL MATLAB SAB REPLICAS?
----------------------------------------

NAHI.

Kafka bolta hai:

ALL ISR REPLICAS

Not:

ALL REPLICAS

Difference samjho.

Example:

Assume ek Topic hai jisme:

Partitions         = 1

Replication Factor = 3

Matlab Partition-0 ki total 3 copies hongi, jo different Brokers par stored hongi.

In 3 replicas me:

* 1 Leader Replica hoga
* 2 Follower Replicas hongi

Replicas:

Leader 
Follower-1
Follower-2

Maan lo currently dono followers completely synced hain with Leader Partition.

Current State:

Leader      Offset = 10
Follower-1  Offset = 10
Follower-2  Offset = 10

Current ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

Ab Producer aur bhi bahut saare messages bhejta hai.

Saare messages Leader tak pahunch jaate hain aur Follower-1 tak bhi successfully replicate ho jaate hain.

Lekin kisi reason se Follower-2 un messages ko receive nahi kar pata aur bahut piche reh jaata hai.

Updated State:

Leader      Offset = 100
Follower-1  Offset = 100
Follower-2  Offset = 40

Ab Follower-2 Leader se kaafi piche hai.

Kafka ise Out Of Sync maanega aur ISR se remove kar dega.

Updated ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1}

Ab Producer:

acks = all

use kar raha hai.


## QUESTION:
--------------

Kya Leader Follower-2 ke sync hone ka bhi wait karega?

Answer:

NO

Leader sirf ISR members ke sync hone ka wait karega.

Is case me:

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1}

To Leader sirf Follower-1 ke sync hone ka wait karega.

Follower-2 ke liye wait nahi karega. Kyuki Follower-2 ISR ka member hi nahi hai.


Important:

acks=all ka matlab:

"Wait for all ISR replicas"

NOT

"Wait for every replica present in the cluster"


## MIN.INSYNC.REPLICAS
-------------------------

Yahi sabse important production setting hai.

Example:

Assume ek Topic hai jisme:

Partitions         = 1
Replication Factor = 3

Matlab Partition-0 ki total 3 copies hongi, jo different Brokers par stored hongi.

In 3 replicas me:

* 1 Leader Replica hoga
* 2 Follower Replicas hongi

Replicas:

Leader
Follower-1
Follower-2

Maan lo currently dono followers completely synced hain with Leader.

Current State:

Leader      Offset = 10
Follower-1  Offset = 10
Follower-2  Offset = 10

Current ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

Producer:

acks=all

use kar raha hai.

Question:

"Producer ko success kab milega?"

Leader replica tabhi ACK bhejega jab message saare current ISR replicas tak replicate ho jaye.
Lekin write accept hogi ya reject, ye min.insync.replicas decide karta hai.


## SCENARIO 1
----------------

Assume:

min.insync.replicas = 2

Matlab write accept karne ke liye kam se kam 2 ISR members hone chahiye.

Current ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

ISR Count = 3

Since, ISR Count (3) ≥ min.insync.replicas (2)

Hence,
-> Write Accepted
-> Producer ko ACK mil jayega.


## SCENARIO 2
-------------

Ab Follower-2 bahut piche reh jata hai ya crash ho jata hai.

Kafka Follower-2 ko ISR se remove kar deta hai.

Updated ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1}

ISR Count = 2

Since, ISR Count (2) ≥ min.insync.replicas (2)

Hence,
-> Write Accepted
-> Producer ko ACK mil jayega.


## SCENARIO 3
----------------
Ab Follower-1 bahut piche reh jata hai ya crash ho jata hai.

Current ISR:

{Leader}

ISR Count = 1

Since, ISR Count (1) < min.insync.replicas (2)

Hence,
-> Write Rejected
-> Producer ko ACK nhi miega.


## KAFKA WRITE REJECT KYU KAR RAHA HAI?
-------------------------------------------

Kafka essentially bol raha hai:

"Mere paas sufficient healthy replicas nahi hain. Main tumhe success nahi bol sakta."

Example:

min.insync.replicas = 2

Lekin currently ISR me sirf:

{Leader}

bacha hua hai.

ISR Count = 1

Agar Kafka is situation me write accept kar le aur Producer ko ACK bhej de and ACK bhejne ke turant baad Leader bhi crash ho jaye, to us message ki koi synchronized copy available nahi hogi.

Result:

Data Loss

Isliye Kafka safety ko priority deta hai aur write reject kar deta hai.

## IMPORTANT:
--------------

Write reject karne se Leader crash hone ki possibility khatam nahi hoti.

Leader phir bhi crash ho sakta hai.

Kafka ka logic hai:

"Jab tak mere paas required number of healthy replicas nahi hain, main write ki durability guarantee nahi kar sakta."

Isliye Kafka write reject karta hai.

In other words, Kafka write reject karke data loss ko impossible nahi banata, balki unsafe writes ko prevent karta hai aur durability guarantees ko maintain karta hai.


## MOST COMMON PRODUCTION CONFIGURATION
-----------------------------------------

Replication Factor = 3

acks = all

min.insync.replicas = 2

Ye configuration high durability aur fault tolerance provide karti hai.

Note : min.insync.replicas is enforced only when the producer uses acks=all.


========================
13: RETENTION POLICY
========================

After a consumer consumes the message from the topic that message is not deleted from the topic (technically partition's of the topic) , 
it stays there unlike other messaging queues like RabbitMQ.

Partition-0
|
|- Offset 0 -> A
|- Offset 1 -> B
|- Offset 2 -> C
|- Offset 3 -> D

Maan lo Consumer ne A, B, C aur D successfully consume kar liye.

Iske baad bhi Partition ka data unchanged rahega

-----------------------------------
## MESSAGES DELETE KAB HOTE HAIN ?
-----------------------------------

Messages kab delete honge, ye Kafka ki Retention Policy decide karti hai.

Kafka data ko do tariko se retain kar sakta hai:

1. Time-Based Retention
   - Data ko ek configured duration (e.g., 7 days) tak retain kiya jata hai.
   - Duration complete hone ke baad purana data delete kar diya jata hai.


2. Size-Based Retention
   - Data ko ek configured storage limit tak retain kiya jata hai.
   - Storage limit exceed hote hi purane messages delete kiye jaate hain.

---------------------------------
KAFKA ME RETENTION SETTINGS:
----------------------------------

1. Broker Level (Global Default)
2. Topic Level (Override)


1: BROKER LEVEL RETENTION (Global Default)
--------------------------------------------

Agar kisi Topic ke liye koi retention policy explicitly define nahi ki gayi hai, to Kafka us Topic par Broker-level retention apply karta hai. 
Yaani, Broker-level retention sabhi Topics ke liye default retention policy ka kaam karti hai.

## NOTE : 
----------
Retention policy Topic ke saare Partitions par apply hoti hai, kisi individual Partition par nahi.

Broker configuration me retention define ki ja sakti hai:

## Time-Based Retention:

   log.retention.hours=170

   ya

   log.retention.ms=604800000

## Size-Based Retention

log.retention.bytes=1073741824


## DEFAULT BROKER LEVEL RETENTION 
----------------------------------

Agar Broker-level retention bhi explicitly configure nahi ki gayi ho, to Kafka default values use karta hai:

## Default Time-Based Retention:
log.retention.hours=168 (Matlab 7 days) 

## Default size-Based Retention:
log.retention.bytes=-1 (Matlab: No size limit)

Matlab koi size limit nahi hai.

Is case me deletion sirf Time-Based Retention ke basis par hogi.

Deletion sirf time-based retention ke basis par hogi.

Yaani agar:

Topic-level retention define nahi hai.
Broker-level retention bhi explicitly configure nahi hai.

to Kafka ye default values use karega.


## TRULY INFINITE RETENTION:
-----------------------------

Agar theoretically data ko indefinitely retain karna ho, to dono limits disable karni padengi:

log.retention.ms=-1
log.retention.bytes=-1

Yaani:

Time-based deletion disabled.
Size-based deletion disabled.

Result: Messages indefinitely retain honge.

Note: Production me aisa configuration generally avoid kiya jata hai, kyunki time ke saath disk storage completely fill ho sakti hai.



2: TOPIC LEVEL RETENTION (Most Common in Production)
--------------------------------------------------------

Topic-level retention configuration broker-level retention ko override kar deti hai.

Yaani agar tumne kisi specific topic par retention define ki hai, to us topic ke liye broker ki retention settings use nahi hongi.

Suppose orders topic me sirf 1 partition hai.

Kafka internally partition ko multiple log segments me divide karke store karta hai.

Partition-0
|
|- Segment-1
|   |
|   |- Offset 0 -> A
|   |- Offset 1 -> B
|   |- Offset 2 -> C
|
|- Segment-2
|    |
|    |- Offset 3 -> D
|    |- Offset 4 -> E
|    |- Offset 5 -> F
|
|-Segment-3
    |
    |- Offset 6 -> G
    |- Offset 7 -> H
    |- Offset 8 -> I


1: TIME BASED RETENTION:
---------------------------

## EXAMPLE:
-------------

@Bean
public NewTopic ordersTopic() {
    return TopicBuilder.name("orders")
            .partitions(3)
            .replicas(3)
            .config(
                TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG,
                TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
            )
            .config(
                TopicConfig.RETENTION_MS_CONFIG,
                String.valueOf(7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) // 7 days
            )
            .build();
}


Explanation:

## TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG
-------------------------------------

Purpose:

-> Kafka Topic ka cleanup behavior configure karne ke liye use hota hai.
-> Is property ke through hum Kafka ko batate hain ki purane records ka
   cleanup kaise karna hai.

Common Values:

1. TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
2. TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT


## TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
-------------------------------------

Meaning: Purana data delete karke cleanup karna hai.


## TopicConfig.RETENTION_MS_CONFIG
-------------------------------------

Meaning: Specified time complete hone ke baad purana eligible segments delete kiya ja sakta hai.

In This Example:

String.valueOf(7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)

-> 7 Days

Meaning:

-> Records ko 7 din tak retain karo.
-> 7 din ke baad eligible segments delete kiye ja sakte hain.

In the above example:

Retention = 7 days

Kafka periodically check karta hai:

"Segment kitna purana hai?"

Current State:

Partition-0

Segment-1 (10 days old)

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C

Segment-2 (5 days old)

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3 (1 day old)

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G

Ab Kafka dekhega:

Segment-1 = 10 days old

Retention = 7 days

To Kafka Segment-1 ko delete kar dega.

Result:

Partition-0

Segment-2

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G


2: SIZE BASED RETENTION :
---------------------------

## EXAMPLE:
-------------

@Bean
public NewTopic ordersTopic() {
    return TopicBuilder.name("orders")
            .partitions(3)
            .replicas(3)
            .config(
                TopicConfig.RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG,
                String.valueOf(10L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024) // 10 GB
            )
            .build();
}

In the above example:

Retention = 10 GB

Kafka periodically check karta hai:

"Total retained data kitna ho gaya hai?"

Current State:

Partition-0

Segment-1 (4 GB) (10 days old)

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C

Segment-2 (5 GB) (5 days old)

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3 (3 GB) (1 day old)

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G

Total Retained Data:

4 GB + 5 GB + 3 GB = 12 GB

Ab Kafka dekhega:

Retention = 10 GB

Current Data = 12 GB

Limit exceed ho chuki hai.

Kafka oldest segment se cleanup start karega.

Is case me:

Segment-1 = 10 days old

To Kafka Segment-1 delete kar dega.

Result:

Partition-0

Segment-2 (5 GB)

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E

Segment-3 (3 GB)

Offset 5 -> F
Offset 6 -> G


## IMPORTANT:
----------------

1: Consumer ne read kiya ya nahi kiya, koi farak nahi padta 
     Deletion sirf time / size ke basis par ho rahi hai.

2: Kafka har segment ke saath timestamp maintain karta hai.
   Generally segment ki age us time se calculate ki jaati hai jab segment create hua tha.

3: Kafka individual messages ya offsets ko delete nahi karta.
   Agar Kafka har message ko offset level par individually delete kare, to disk operations bahut expensive aur inefficient ho jayengi.
   Isliye Kafka segment-level deletion use karta hai, jo high-throughput systems ke liye kaafi efficient approach hai.


======================
14. LOG COMPACTION
======================

Retention ka Goal:
-> Storage bachana
-> Purana data delete karna

Compaction ka Goal:
-> Har key ki latest value bacha ke rakhna
-> Purani history corresponding to us key delete ho sakti hai


Log Compaction sirf tab useful hai jab messages ke paas KEY ho. Producer jab message publish karta hai to optionally ek KEY bhi pass kar sakta hai.

Ye KEY do kaam karti hai:

1. Partition decide karne me help karti hai
   partition = hash(key) % number_of_partitions

2. Compaction ke time Kafka isi KEY ka use karta hai ye identify karne ke liye
   ki kaunse records same entity ko represent karte hain.


ONE-LINE DEFINITION :
Log Compaction is a Kafka cleanup strategy that retains the latest record
for each key while allowing older records with the same key to be removed.


## EXAMPLE :
-------------

Maan lo ek Topic hai:

Topic = UserLocation

Aur Topic ke paas 2 Partitions hain:

UserLocation
|
|- Partition-0
|- Partition-1


Producer messages publish karta hai:

(Key=User1, Value=Delhi)
(Key=User1, Value=Mumbai)
(Key=User1, Value=Bangalore)

Meaning:

User1 pehle Delhi me tha
phir Mumbai shift hua
phir Bangalore shift hua


Kyuki teeno messages ki KEY same hai:

Key = User1

Isliye teeno messages same Partition me jayenge.

Suppose: Partition-0

Partition-0
|
Offset 0:
|   |- Key   = User1
|   |- Value = Delhi
|
|
Offset 1:
|   |- Key   = User1
|   |- Value = Mumbai
|
Offset 2:
    |- Key   = User1
    |- Value = Bangalore


## QUESTION :
-------------

Current City kya hai?

Answer: Bangalore


To Delhi aur Mumbai kyun rakhe hue hain?

Answer:

Historical tracking ke liye useful ho sakte hain.

Lekin kai systems ko history nahi chahiye.

Unhe sirf latest state chahiye.


## REAL WORLD EXAMPLE :
--------------------------

Topic:

CustomerPreferences

Messages:

(Key=User1, Value=Hindi)
(Key=User1, Value=English)
(Key=User1, Value=French)

Current Preference: French

Yahan Hindi aur English ki value ab business ke liye useful nahi hai.

Hume sirf latest state chahiye.


## COMPACTION ENABLE KARTE HAIN
---------------------------------

##EXAMPLE
----------

@Bean
public NewTopic userProfileTopic() {
      return TopicBuilder.name("user-profile")
        .partitions(3)
        .replicas(3)
        .config(
            TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG,
            TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT
        )
        .build();
}


## TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_COMPACT
-------------------------------------

-> Log Compaction enable karta hai.
-> Har KEY ki latest value preserve karta hai.
-> Same KEY ke purane records eventually remove ho sakte hain.
-> Ye cleanup strategy hai.


------------------------------------
## KYA COMPACTION INSTANT HOTA HAI ?
------------------------------------

Answer: Compaction instant nahi hota.

Compaction ek background process hai. Kafka background me periodically cleanup run karta hai.

Kafka instant cleanup ki guarantee nahi deta.


