## RESULT
-----------

- Consumer har baar same message read karega.
- Business processing har baar fail hogi.
- Offset commit nahi hoga.
- Kafka message ko baar-baar re-deliver karega.

Ye infinite processing loop create kar sakta hai.

Isi problematic message ko Poison Message kehte hain.


## AT LEAST ONCE ME POISON MESSAGE KO KAISE HANDLE KAROGE?
------------------------------------------------------------

Answer: Application Retries + Dead Letter Topic (DLT)

## APPROACH :
-------------

1. Business processing ko fixed number of retries do.

Example:

Retry-1 ❌
Retry-2 ❌
Retry-3 ❌

(Ye retries application/framework, jaise Spring Kafka, perform karta hai.)

2. Agar saare retries fail ho jaayein, to message ko Dead Letter Topic (DLT) me publish kar do.

3. Ensure karo ki message successfully DLT me publish ho gaya hai.

4. Original message ka offset commit kar do.

5. Consumer next message ki processing continue karega.


## BENEFITS :
--------------

✔ Infinite re-delivery loop avoid hota hai.

✔ Consumer poison message ki wajah se block nahi hota.

✔ Baaki messages ki processing continue rehti hai.

✔ Problematic messages ko baad me analyze aur reprocess kiya ja sakta hai.


