15. HIGH WATERMARK
===============================================================================

High Watermark ka purpose hai Consumers ko sirf wahi messages dikhana jo Leader Replica par successfully store ho chuke hon
aur us Partition ki current ISR me maujood sabhi Follower Replicas tak bhi successfully replicate ho chuke hon.


## IMPORTANT
--------------

High Watermark ka concept tabhi meaningful hota hai jab Replication enabled ho.

Agar:

Replication Factor = 1

matlab Partition ki sirf ek hi Replica (Leader Replica) exist karti hai aur koi Follower Replica nahi hota.

Is case me:

High Watermark = Leader Replica ka Last Offset (LEO)

Yaani, Replication Factor = 1 ke case me High Watermark practically Leader Replica ke Last Offset (LEO) ke barabar hota hai.

Isliye Leader Replica par jo bhi messages successfully persist ho jaate hain, wo turant Consumers ke liye visible ho jaate hain.


## IMPORTANT
--------------

High Watermark calculate karte waqt Kafka Partition ki sabhi Replicas ko consider nahi karta.

Ye sirf current ISR (In-Sync Replicas) ke basis par calculate hota hai.


## EXAMPLE
------------

Maan lo:

Topic = orders

Aur is Topic ke paas sirf ek Partition hai:

orders
   |
   +----> Partition-0

Aur:

Replication Factor = 3

Assume karo Cluster me 3 Brokers hain aur Partition-0 ki Replicas un Brokers me distributed hain:

Broker-1 -> Leader Replica

Broker-2 -> Follower Replica

Broker-3 -> Follower Replica

Maan lo Consumer-1 ne `orders` Topic ko subscribe kar rakha hai.

Producer ne 10 messages publish kiye aur wo current ISR ki sabhi Replicas tak successfully replicate ho gaye.

Current State:

Leader Replica       Offset = 10

Follower Replica-1   Offset = 10

Follower Replica-2   Offset = 10

Current ISR:

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

Kyuki current ISR ke sabhi members Offset 10 tak synchronized hain,

isliye:

High Watermark = 10


## NEW MESSAGE ARRIVES
-----------------------

Ab Producer ek aur message publish karta hai:

Offset 11 -> D

Ye message Leader Replica par successfully store ho jata hai.

Lekin abhi tak Followers tak replicate nahi hua.

Current State:

Leader Replica       Offset = 11

Follower Replica-1   Offset = 10

Follower Replica-2   Offset = 10


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
## QUESTION: WILL CONSUMER-1 BE ABLE TO READ MESSAGE 'D'? IF NOT, WHY?
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Answer: NO.

Kyuki message 'D' abhi tak current ISR ke sabhi Replicas tak successfully replicate nahi hua hai.

Isliye:

High Watermark = 10

hi rahega.

Aur Kafka ka ek important rule hai:

**Consumer sirf High Watermark tak ke messages hi read kar sakta hai.**

Matlab:

Offset <= High Watermark

tak ke messages hi Consumer ko visible honge.


## BUT WHY?
------------

Suppose Kafka Consumer ko message 'D' read karne de deta.

Ab maan lo:

Leader Replica (Broker-1) crash ho jaati hai.

Ab current ISR me se koi Follower naya Leader banega.

Example:

Follower-1 -> New Leader

Current State:

Leader Replica       Offset = 10

Follower Replica-2   Offset = 10

Message 'D' permanently lost ho jayega.

Ab Consumer kahega:

"Maine 'D' read kiya tha."

Lekin Kafka ke paas wo message exist hi nahi karega.

Ye data inconsistency create kar dega.

**Isi situation ko avoid karne ke liye Kafka Consumers ko kabhi bhi High Watermark se aage ka data read nahi karne deta.**


## AB MAAN LO
--------------

Ab maan lo ki Follower-1 bhi Leader Replica se message replicate kar leta hai, lekin Follower-2 bahut piche reh jata hai aur Kafka use ISR se remove kar deta hai.

Old ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

New ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1}

Current State:

Leader Replica       Offset = 11

Follower Replica-1   Offset = 11

Isliye:

High Watermark = 11

ho jayega.

Ab Consumer ko:

Offset 11 -> D

visible ho jayega.


## IMPORTANT
--------------

ISR ka matlab ye nahi hota ki:

Leader Offset == Follower Offset

har microsecond ya har instant par exactly same hon.

Kafka Followers ko thoda sa lag (replication delay) karne ki permission deta hai.

Jab tak Followers acceptable limits (defined by `replica.lag.time.max.ms`) ke andar Leader ke saath synchronized rehte hain, tab tak wo ISR ka part bane rehte hain.

Example:

Leader Replica       Offset = 100

Follower Replica-1   Offset = 99

Follower Replica-2   Offset = 99

Aur phir bhi:

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

ho sakta hai.

Yaani ISR ka matlab **perfectly identical offsets nahi, balki Leader ke saath sufficiently synchronized Replicas hota hai.
